{<prologue}
<div>
	<p>
		Dust refers to the data used to render a template as a context. The context is modelled as a stack of Javascript objects, 
		arrays, and literals. Dust can search multiple layers of the stack, popping off the top objects and looking below.
	</p>
	<p>
		In this example, Dust moves “up” the context stack.	
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>The context is set to a single child inside the #children section.</li>	 
   	<li>Dust finds the child’s firstName at that context level.</li>	 
   	<li>Dust can’t find a lastName at the child’s context level, so it moves up one level and searches again.</li>	 
	</ul>
</div>
{/prologue}
